The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Commerce and industry minister Nirupam Sen will inaugurate the revamped factory of Gluconate India Health Limited on March 15 at Dum Dum Cantonment, on the northern fringes of the city. The state government undertaking began incurring losses in the past decade. A revamp process was initiated after 220 employees opted for early retirement. Around Rs 3 crore has been spent to procure sophisticated equipment for the unit.

 Raymond Kenneth Thomas, a Seychelles national, was arrested at the airport late on Monday. Thomas was wanted by Mumbai police in connection with a criminal case. He was arrested while he was about to board a Singapore Airlines flight.

 The CID on Tuesday received an interim report of the narco-analysis test conducted in Bangalore in the Ganesh Palodhi murder case. The report said Siddhartha Palodhi, Ganeshs father, had confessed during the test that he had mixed dhatura flower extract with the soft drink served to his four-year-old son to kill him. The Central Forensic Laboratory, which had conducted the test, would soon send a full report, along with a CD containing the details, to the investigating agency.

 A gang of seven was arrested in Jadavpur on Tuesday on charges of hoarding foreign liquor to sell it in the black market. Around 50 litres of liquor were seized from them. The raid followed a tip-off. Police said the gang had been operating for a long time.

 A man and a woman were arrested at Kanchrapara railway station, on the northern fringes of the city, on Tuesday evening on charges of immoral trafficking. A Government Railway Police officer said Ganesh Basak and Saraswati Ghose were on their way to Bihar to sell off two minors. 

 Chhatra Parishad supporters staged a demonstration outside Writers Buildings on Tuesday afternoon to protest the murder of a Congress leader, allegedly by a police officer, in Katwa, Burdwan, on February 25. Police said 54 protesters, including five women, were arrested and brought to the central lock-up in Lalbazar. Three women were injured in a scuffle with police.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will meet physically-challenged students at a programme in Mukandapur, on the southern fringes of the city, on March 9. The three-day programme, organised by the Rajya Pratibandhi Sammelani and the state mass education department, starts on March 8.

